12,63,0,3496,-911,1270,241,8,7,0,8,-1,0,0,0,-1--1--1,-1--1--1,|24||0-0-0,0,0,0,0,0,0
This module represents the core economic structure of the model, focusing on the calculation of Gross Domestic Product (GDP) and its main components: Expected GDP, Real Value Added, Compensation of Employees, Gross Operational Surplus, and Net Exports. The module enables GDP calculation through multiple approaches, such as summing employee compensation and operational surplus or adjusting real value added with taxes and subsidies on products. It also includes scarcity factors that limit real production per sector due to constraints in critical resources like water, energy, food, and labor. This module is essential for projecting economic performance under various scenarios, providing a detailed view of income distribution across productive sectors and the impact of fiscal policies on GDP.
